  "name": "Luke 20:45–21:4",
  "localizedName": "Luke 20:45–21:4",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus warned the people of Israel not to trust their religious leaders. Most of the leaders didn’t love God and serve him with sincere hearts. They were greedy and didn’t show mercy."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The leaders would take over widows’ houses when they couldn’t pay what they owed."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Then Jesus praised a widow who gave an offering of money to God. Her small offering was all that she had. By giving everything, the widow showed how deeply she trusted God to take care of her."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
